A text-output rule that formats one ledger entry per input record.
The line is built from two intermediate text let bindings: a tagged
identifier mixing the user name and entry id, then the full line
mixing the tagged id with the amount and a literal suffix. Neither
let RHS is a pure text literal — both are concat(...) — so this is
the first example whose native binary is only possible after Phase 2I
(non-literal text let bindings). Before 2I, the same output had to
be written as a single monolithic concat at the return site.
